OL,3,CActors from the show 'An Officer and a
OL,4,CGentleman' get training from military
OL,6,F"Very impressed," said Second
OL,7,FLieutenant Reuben James. "I think
OL,8,Fthey'd make pretty good recruits. I
OL,9,Fthink the army and army reserves would
OL,10,Fbe glad to have them on board.J"It's a
OL,11,Fbit of last minute method acting to
OL,12,Fhelp them get into the zone for their
OL,13,Fappearance in a very popular show."
OL,15,FWhile Second Lt James was impressed
OL,16,Fwith the the stage stars, some of the
OL,17,Factors admitted to ITV Tyne Tees that
OL,18,F'it's very intense,' and 'slightly
OL,19,Fterrifying.' They did, however, admit
OL,20,Fit was good to get an insight into the
OL,21,Fmilitary.
