OL,3,CActors from the show 'An Officer and a
OL,4,CGentleman' get training from military
OL,6,FTalking about into stepping in the the
OL,7,Fshoes of the lead character Zack Mayo
OL,8,Fwho was originally played by Gere,
OL,9,FLuke Baker said: "It's tough. You want
OL,10,Fto represent the role as well as you
OL,11,Fcan. But you've got to make it your
OL,12,Fown as well. You do your research on
OL,13,Fthe character and bring it to life and
OL,14,Fbe truthful."JLiv Foster- Browne
OL,15,Fadded: "It's one of those shows where
OL,16,Fyou know the audience are with you.
OL,17,FPeople that come to see it usually
OL,18,Fhave seen the movie and are they
OL,19,Fbecause they love the film, love the
OL,20,Fstoryline. So they are with you from
OL,21,Fthe get go."JThe character Sid Worley
OL,22,Fis played by Paul French who said:
OL,23,F"The iconic last scene, how the show
OL,24,Fends, when Luke comes in his whites to
OL,25,Fsweep Paula off her feet the place
OL,26,Freally does go ballistic."
